.nh
.TH "TAKO" "1" "Jun 2026" "Tako CLI" "Tako CLI Manual"

.SH NAME
tako-proxy-hash-password - Mint a bcrypt hash for proxy.basicAuth.passwordBcrypt


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBtako proxy hash-password [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Hash a password for proxy basic authentication.

.PP
The config takes a pre-computed bcrypt hash instead of a plaintext password so
the hash stays stable across deploys (bcrypt salts fresh hashes differently on
every call, which would churn proxy state). Reads the password from the
terminal without echo, or from stdin when piped.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB--cost\fP=10
	bcrypt cost factor

.PP
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for hash-password


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--config\fP=""
	config file (default is ./tako.yaml or ./tako.json)

.PP
\fB-e\fP, \fB--env\fP=""
	environment to deploy (default: production or only environment)

.PP
\fB--events\fP=""
	stream progress events to stdout: ndjson (human output moves to stderr)

.PP
\fB--host-key-mode\fP=""
	SSH host key verification mode: tofu, strict, ask (default: tofu)

.PP
\fB--output\fP="text"
	output format: text or json (json reserves stdout for the final result document)

.PP
\fB-v\fP, \fB--verbose\fP[=false]
	verbose output


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  tako proxy hash-password
  echo -n "s3cret" | tako proxy hash-password
  tako proxy hash-password --output json
.EE


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBtako-proxy(1)\fP
